Your logic why the pack is expensive is correct, but some of your facts are wrong.  First, you don't kill a goblin runner to get the pouch, you kill a Grimling Runner.  Second, he is on a 90 minute spawn time, not a 45 minute spawn time.  Third, he does not spawn in Grimling Forest.  He spawns in Tenebrous Mountains in the cave that leads to Grimling Forest.  He is lvl 35 and is immune to any spells that slow his run speed such as snare or root spells.  He drops a pouch that is NO DROP.  This gets turned into Rallic in Katta Castellum who gives you the Rallic Pack Pattern.  You must then tailor your own pack with the required ingredients, which includes a Perfect Owlbear Pelt which is a rare drop, plus some easy swatch and chord items.  Otherwise, you had a good post.  I hope this helps anyone trying to find him.

